text.__SUMMARY__:
Eucalyptus suggrandis is a mallee that is native to a large area along the south coast of Western Australia.The mallee typically grows to a height of 1 to 5 metres (3 to 16 ft) and has smooth grey-copper coloured bark. It blooms between November and March producing inflorescences with cream-white flowers.
It is found on sandplains, rises, along drainage lines and in breakaways in the Goldfields-Esperance and Wheatbelt regions where it grows in sandy-clay-loam soils over quartzite, laterite or granite.
